Fuchimori was hospitalized again for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fuchimori was hospitalized on Tuesday at a state hospital to examine the loss of muscle strength that is being observed in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fuchimori, 72, who was sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from a number of diseases, including tongue cancer, which caused him to undergo surgery four times and is under surveillance.
Congressman Alejandro Aginaga, who is his personal doctor, told TV channel N that Fuchimori will be examined in three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases to determine the cause of pain and loss of strength in his lower limbs.
Aginaga said that in his opinion, Fuchimori should be a candidate for a pardon for humanitarian reasons; however, he said he does not want it because he knows he is innocent.
He carried out four operations on tongue cancer, lost 18 kilograms of weight, to which were added other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreatic cysts, kidney stones, high blood pressure and problems with blood circulation in the legs.
Fuchimori has been in prison since September 2007, in the National Police Department of Special Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the killing of 25 people by an army destroyer, which acted secretly during the first years of his reign.
